[50.098108, "o", "\r\n"]
[50.405014, "o", "\r\n  Model                  Vanilla    + Optimized Prompt    Δ\r\n  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n  Llama 3.1  8B          87%        87%                   —\r\n  Mistral Small  24B     87%        90%                   +3pp\r\n  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n\r\n"]
[52.910771, "o", "\u001b[2m# 90% on Mistral with the prompt — matching what the baseline agent needed\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[53.515414, "o", "\u001b[2m# 21 rounds of meta-optimization to achieve. Prompts are portable capital.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[56.624446, "o", "\u001b[2m# So what does this actually teach us about AI agents?\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[58.030792, "o", "\u001b[0;32mabhi@thinkpad\u001b[0m:\u001b[0;34m~/meta-agent-improver\u001b[0m$ c"]
[58.068823, "o", "a"]
[58.107502, "o", "t"]
[58.146023, "o", " "]
[58.185705, "o", "L"]
[58.227628, "o", "E"]
[58.265762, "o", "A"]
[58.302645, "o", "R"]
[58.341395, "o", "N"]
[58.379569, "o", "I"]
[58.417668, "o", "N"]
[58.454602, "o", "G"]
[58.492101, "o", "S"]
[58.530263, "o", "."]
[58.568059, "o", "m"]
[58.605123, "o", "d"]
[58.642933, "o", "\r\n"]
[58.946298, "o", "\r\n\u001b[0;33m1. Failures are free training data.\u001b[0m\r\n   Every failed iteration gave the meta-agent a signal about what\r\n   not to do. After 21 runs, it knew the shape of the problem better\r\n   than any human reviewer could sketch in a doc.\r\n\r\n"]
[60.449282, "o", "\u001b[0;33m2. Small models + good prompts rival larger ones.\u001b[0m\r\n   Mistral Small 24B with the optimized prompt hit 90% pass rate —\r\n   matching what the baseline inner model achieved after full\r\n   meta-optimization. Prompts are portable capital.\r\n\r\n"]
[61.952838, "o", "\u001b[0;33m3. Prompt edits must be length-neutral.\u001b[0m\r\n   Adding 200 chars of new guidance broke tasks that were already\r\n   passing. The fix: for every N characters added, remove N from\r\n   somewhere else. Attention budgets are real.\r\n\r\n"]
[63.455937, "o", "\u001b[0;33m4. Hardware rewrites architecture; schedules survive.\u001b[0m\r\n   Depth=8 loses on A40 by 0.004, wins on H100 by 0.046.\r\n   But LR schedules (warmdown 0.7, LR floor 5%) help on every GPU.\r\n   Good meta-agents should prefer hardware-independent levers.\r\n\r\n"]
[66.459628, "o", "\u001b[2m# Everything was built in one weekend. ~$26 total.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
